Name: The University Of Memphis
Description: At the University of Memphis, we are Driven by Doing. Driven by Doing isn't just a slogan. It's what you'll see happening all around you at the UofM. Every. Single. Day. We've had a lot of firsts here in Memphis. But our most memorable years are yet to come. We are all about forward progress. Yours. That's what Memphis does.    For over 100 years, the UofM has been a catalyst for progress in the city of Memphis, the state of Tennessee and the surrounding Mid-South region. From its inception in 1912 as a “normal school” dedicated to the education of public school teachers to its role today as an educator of technologically savvy, socially conscious graduates who face a complex world, the UofM has always been an integral component of the greater community.    Exceptional students from 50 states and 82 countries choose the University of Memphis as their collegiate home.  Approximately 22,000 students attend the UofM, including more than 2,200 first-time freshmen and 2,500 students who live in university housing.      In 2013, U.S. News & World Report ranked the University of Memphis among the top 10 in the country for student internship placements and lauded it as one of the top 13 for its teacher preparation programs. Additionally, its graduate programs in audiology, speech-language pathology and rehabilitation counseling are consistently ranked among the top 20 in the nation by U.S. News.    As a doctoral-granting metropolitan research university, the UofM is committed to excellence in undergraduate, graduate and professional education; in the discovery and dissemination of knowledge; in engaged scholarship to the community, state and nation; and in the preparation of a diverse student population for successful careers and meaningful participation in a global society.    Ever forward looking, the University of Memphis is poised to enter one of its most historic and productive periods. Having just celebrated its centennial anniversary, its faculty, staff, alumn...

Name: The Ronin Group
Description: Just because you own your own or aspire to own a business does not mean you are an entrepreneur.  Academically, Merriam-Webster defines the owner through the lens of possession while defining an entrepreneur through the lens of the activities involved in owning, managing, and running a business. A business owner might buy into or start a business because "it was a great opportunity, or it's the only thing I enjoy doing or know how to do." An entrepreneur will say things like, "I saw a better way of doing things," or "I saw a gap or a need in the industry. Whether you want to be a business owner or an entrepreneur, we are dedicated to seeing you succeed. Since our conception, the Ronin Group LLC has been dedicated to small businesses' development and success nationwide. We excel at assisting inspiring business owners and entrepreneurs in taking their vision and turning it into the reality of a viable and functioning business. The Ronin Group can assist in developing, growing, and/or restructuring your business, acquiring new methods, or operating procedures to achieve organizational excellence. The Ronin Group is responsible for a wide range of functions, with the content of roles varying significantly from customer to customer.  At The Ronin Group, we have access to the skill sets and experience essential for your business development. Our specialists consist of a mixture of sales, finance, marketing, legal, strategic management, vision, corporate structure, land development, business administration, standard operating procedures, retail merchandising, government contracting and proposal writing, and permitting and licensing. Our process incorporates meetings to discuss your vision; the Ronin Group team will develop a course of action by phases specifically to meet your needs and goals.  Once a plan is approved by you, we will move forward with the agreed-upon schedule. You will be keep apprised of our progress through emails and daily/ weekly discussions with you.

Name: UroSense
Description: Did you know that catheter-associated infections (CAUTIs) create a £100 million economic burden on the NHS annually? Not only that, but due to the flawed design of the presently active Foley catheters, thousands of patients lose their lives each year as a result of CAUTI related issues. This is concerning seeing as CAUTI is ranked the most prevalent hospital-associated infection in the UK.   UroSense, a recently-founded medical device company based in the United Kingdom, is on a mission to innovate the current Foley catheter. The aim is to improve the striking UK catheter-associated urinary infection (CAUTI) rates, with the ultimate goal being to also see improvements in global CAUTI rates.  How will we achieve this? With our team of competent and skilled individuals including medics, engineers and microbiologists, we are looking to redesign the current Foley catheter. Having lacked innovation for over 80 years, it is time that a new approach is taken on Foley catheters in order to tackle the pertinent and life-changing issue that is CAUTI.

Name: tom_mark.
Description: Think about where you are.  The place.  The environment.   How does it make you feel?   Distracted?  Excited?  Calm?    One of the things I love about London is its variety. As you move from one place to another it always makes you feel a bit different. Sometimes the simplest things can spark an interest, emotion or action.   Like when you're at Wembley Stadium and your team scores. You shout at the top of your voice, maybe even spontaneously hugging the stranger next to you.  Or when you’ve just walked into your favourite cafe, your face tingles from the sudden warmth, the coffee smell welcomes you and within moments, you feel relaxed and safe.  All these places influence you, triggering a wash of emotions that starts actions.  Now imagine your brand is a place.    How would you describe it? What emotions would it trigger? Who would you make it for?   I believe that every brand can be unique; you just have to get to know it, hear its story, extract and combine all the elements that prove its quality…  And make it remarkable.    And that’s what we do.  (Brand Positioning Statement) Tom Mark is a design studio based in London, creating authentic visual branding stories across all disciplines through unique DRC methodology. For anyone wanting to leave their mark on the world.

Name: Vesynta
Description: Vesynta focuses on precise dosing, that is personal and targeted to the patient’s individual characteristics.  Our technology combines automated desktop hardware with analytical software to provide a universal platform for medicine exposure analysis from patient blood.  Your health is personal, so why isn't your treatment?  Physicians currently determine your medicine dose based upon your body weight or size. Unfortunately, this approach fails to consider the large variability in how individual patients distribute, break-down and clear drugs from the body.   There are many complicating factors which contribute to this variance, including gender, age, ethnicity, nutrition and well-being, none of which are accounted for using traditional dosing approaches.   This leads to inconsistencies between patients in terms of how much drug is achieved in the blood and how long the drugs stay there - also known as medicine exposure.  The end result is patients suffering from poorly treated conditions or dealing with life-limiting side effects associated with critical medicine.  Patients groups that especially suffer with the ‘one size fits all’ approach include: - Paediatrics (under 16 years of age) - Geriatrics (over 65 years of age) - Anephric groups  - Patients on dose intense treatment schedules - Patients with rare genetic disorders - Patients on narrow therapeutic index drugs  Physicians are seeking to implement approaches of routine treatment modifications according to patient response. However, a lack of real-time patient data makes this practice a clinical challenge.   Our purpose is to elevate the safety and effectiveness of medicines in these groups and others. Through revolutionising bedside patient monitoring, we can generate medicine exposure data to enable individualised treatment for better health outcomes.
Headquarters: Torrington Place,Office 203a, Roberts Engineering Building,England,London,United Kingdom

Name: Pure Headshots
Description: Welcome to Pure Headshots, a specialist headshot photographer based in Berkshire, but regularly shooting in London, Buckinghamshire, Oxfordshire, Surrey, Hampshire and Wiltshire. We’ve been shooting headshots for over five years working with actors, acting schools (The Reel Scene), models, and corporate clients across the UK.  The headshot has never been more important in our ever increasingly visual world. The rise of social media combined with the smartphone selfie means that headshots are everywhere and we are being judged on what we upload to the internet. Whether you are an aspiring actor adding a new headshot to your spotlight profile or a company updating headshots on their 'about' page then it’s important to think about what the image says about you. As the name of our studio suggest, we are focused on the purity and honesty of the headshot. It may sound obvious, but a headshot must actually look like you! The biggest mistake a client can make is to expect a photographer to mis-represent or over glamorise them - the last thing a casting director or agent wants is to invite you to an audition and then someone walks through the door who is unrecognisable from the image in front of them. It is our job at Pure Headshots to use our photographic knowledge, experience of lighting, direction and industry expertise, to accurately photograph you at your very best so your headshot ‘pops off the page’.

Name: Kola Project
Description: In the fast-paced, consumerist world we live in, it is easy to forget how our actions impact the earth. We often hear about fast fashion and how it is detrimental to the environment—but what about fast furniture? We get it. People change, and so do their tastes in home decor. That rustic coffee table you bought a few years ago no longer matches your taste for sleek, modern decor now.  You could easily throw it out, but what is the hidden cost of doing this? The EPA estimates that there are over 10 million tons of furniture waste thrown out every year, and this number is climbing. At Kola Project, we believe that a win for your stylish kitchen or living room doesn't have to be a loss for the environment.  This is what sets us apart from our competitors. Our unlimited take-back program ensures that every piece of unwanted or broken furniture that you give us will be repurposed into something useful and resold. And we'll reward you for doing this!  What else sets us apart?  * Small-scale manufacturing ensures you get handmade or unique designs and high-quality furniture that is more durable.  *Minimalist, biodegradable packaging that gets rid of the wasteful bubble wrap and styrofoam.  *Affordable pieces. Typically, high-quality, luxury furniture with a sustainable approach would cost a lot more.  * Locally sourced materials and suppliers, that are mostly based in Europe.  * No low-quality synthetic woods and vinyl materials that you'll have to throw out in a few months.  * 95% materials are plastic-free  Discover unique homeware pieces and learn about the world of waste-free homeware shopping at our Kola Project website. We also plan to create an experimental showroom in London in 2021 to help you better visualize how they would look in your home.

Name: Dm Drogerie Markt Slovenija
Description: Mednarodno uspešno podjetje dm drogerie markt je eno največjih drogerijskih podjetij v srednji in jugovzhodni Evropi. Z več kot 3.700 prodajalnami je podjetje zastopano v 13 evropskih državah. Celoten koncern nudi več kot 62.600 delovnih mest.  V Sloveniji podjetje zaposluje več kot 800 ljudi. Prvo prodajalno v Sloveniji smo v ljubljanskem nakupovalnem središču BTC odprli leta 1993, danes pa se ponašamo z več kot 90 prodajalnami v več kot 50 krajih širom države.   Široka ponudba izdelkov in storitev Potrebe ljudi igrajo za dm pomembno vlogo, zato se svojim strankam trudimo nuditi le najboljše: ugodne cene ter široko ponudbo kakovostnih izdelkov in storitev. Od leta 2020 stranke lahko nakupujejo tudi prek spletne trgovine, prav tako pa v centru lepote dm Studio v Kranju ponujamo frizersko-kozmetične storitve.  V 94 prodajalnah po Sloveniji nudimo približno 13.500 različnih izdelkov, med katerimi je več kot 4.300 izdelkov lastnih blagovnih znamk. Z našimi znamkami, ki obsegajo področja nege telesa, kozmetike, higienskih izdelkov, medicinskih pripomočkov, prehranskih dodatkov, nege otroka in dojenčka, korekcijskih pripomočkov, gospodinjstva, fotostoritev in živali, smo prepričali že na stotisoče strank.   Doživite delo drugače V podjetju dm sodelavci delo doživijo drugače, saj ne opravljajo svojih delovnih nalog le po vnaprej predpisanih in ustaljenih tirnicah. Sodelavci vidijo sebe kot del ekipe in sami oblikujejo svoje delovno okolje. Nudimo vam delo, ki je drugačno in ki ga boste vsak dan opravljali z iskrico v očeh. S svojimi idejami in sposobnostmi boste prispevali pri uresničitvi našega temeljnega cilja, ki je navduševanje strank z našo ponudbo in storitvami. Delo, ki ga opravljamo z navdušenjem in ponosom, je namreč temelj uspešnih dolgoročnih sodelovanj. Podjetje dm Slovenija je med drugim prejemnik nagrade za uglednega delodajalca v panogi maloprodaja, ki jo je decembra 2019 podelil največji zaposlitveni portal MojeDelo.com.   Kupujem tam kjer nekaj veljam

Name: The Sundial Journal
Description: The Sundial Journal is an independent publication committed to shedding light on unheard stories. For young people.  Growing up, we struggled to find a platform where we could freely express our views. We needed somewhere to channel our thoughts and opinions, but the inaccessibility of mainstream media meant that this felt unattainable.   During the lockdown of Summer 2020 (after eating an obscene amount of banana bread!) we did a lot of thinking. Lockdown, with all its ups and downs, became a time of creation, innovation and exploration, with young people leading the way. A place for young people to be seen, heard and celebrated seemed more important than ever. So, after much planning, The Sundial Journal was born.  The Sundial Journal is a place for young people to write honestly on all things, from global news, to what’s trending on Twitter. It is a platform that welcomes young people of all backgrounds and experiences.  Our sections are News (non-mainstream news and local news), Thoughts (opinion-based pieces), Favourites (for Lifestyle reviews), and Gallery (a multimedia section of art, poetry, and other young people’s work).  We are currently a volunteer-led publication, so unfortunately we cannot offer any payment, but this is something we hope to change in the future. If you would like to donate, please email us at sundialjournal@gmail.com.  SUBMISSIONS ARE NOW OPEN. Name: Palion Medical
Description: We are a medical device company focused on developing precision medicine solutions that improve outcomes and minimise side effects.  Developed from research at the Norwegian University of Science and Technology and St. Olav's University Hospital, Trondheim our initial product, Multiguide, is a highly precise injection system that is partnered with a proprietary, simple & easy to use handheld neuro-navigation system to deliver nerve blocks for the treatment of severe headache disorders.  Our belief is that this technology will significantly lower the cost and complexity associated with image guided interventions and by facilitating a shift from general to local anaesthesia, increase intervention accessibility. As a result, MultiGuide & miniNAV may represent a shift from highly specialised procedures performed by few, to easy-to-perform procedures within the reach of any surgeon or physician.   These significant advantages open possibilities not yet seen for image guide procedures and our aim is to develop our technology for a variety of procedures involving image guided navigation.

THE CONCEPT  The world’s growing population has resulted in an increased demand for space and resources, both of which are getting scarce. Similar effects can be witnessed in urban cities, where accommodations are getting smaller to contain the increasing populace. Transforming furniture is a solution that makes better and efficient use of the available space.  Metropolitan Collection  Elements that unfold make it possible to keep everything compact, leaving the interior bright and open. Opting for skinny framed furniture allows all-important daylight to flow right through a room, while heavier set furniture can block out the light.  The collection creates choice in how a person sets up the interior. Having a minimal amount of storage space, a high variety of furniture layout options are easily accessible.

Name: Sognef,.
Description: Innumerous scientific studies have conclusively proven that early diagnosis can exponentially increase the chances of survival and successful treatment. As it stands now, it is obvious that early diagnostics is possible, however, there are practical challenges in terms of the accessibility and extensiveness of the actual test. Sognef was founded with the intent of providing a solution to a necessity that has been overlooked for decades because of the regimented shape of the industry where costs are high, automation and accessibility are low, consolidation and comprehensiveness is absent, and markets are geared towards specialized physicians preventing proper and effective early diagnostics/screening.   Sognef’s vision is to have one, single liquid biopsy-based test that can provide early stage diagnostics for cancers, cardiovascular, neurodegenerative, infectious, and rare diseases in a consolidated, cost-effective, simple, and practical manner. Around three to five years from now, when Sognef has developed diagnostic profiles or indications for all of its possible target diseases, the goal is to be able to provide any individual with a single blood test that can screen them for a whole range of diseases from common to uncommon to rare in a manner that is affordable, simple, and accurate. In the event that the individual who is regularly taking tests, develops a disease or condition (i.e. pancreatic cancer, Alzheimer’s, COPD), Sognef will be able to catch it in its earliest stages.

Name: XTI-360
Description: XTI-360™, by American PPE & CleanCoating, is a world-exclusive, continuously acting, anti-germ, nanocoating technology, that provides a protective barrier, killing and vaporizing dangerous virus and bacteria germs upon contact. With > 99.99% efficacy (US SGS lab tested), XTI-360™ is free of any chemical binders and leaves no toxic residue from dead germs. The self-cleaning coating works continuously, 24/7, and one treatment lasts for at least one year. It can be applied to virtually any surface, indoors and out, including metal, plastic, glass, electronics, fabric, ceramic, stone, tile, wood, and textiles. The coating is 100% green, non-toxic, non-flammable, and RoHS compliant, so it can be used on surfaces common in the hospitality industry, such as food preparation and storage stations, and, XTI-360™ can keep guest rooms allergy-free. In addition to preventing surface transmission of germs and viruses, XTI-360™ can also be used to combat the spread of harmful airborne microbes. When applied to components of a building’s HVAC system, such as ducts and filters, the coating continuously kills virus and bacteria germs in recirculating air as they pass through a facility’s ventilation systems. This also assists facilities in killing all odors, including smoke and those associated with pet-friendly rooms. American PPE & CleanCoating also manufactures commercial quantities of high-quality, medical masks, meeting all requirements for FDA certification (customers can specify L1, L2, or L3) and providing at least 95 percent filtration. All products are made in the USA. No masks or materials will be from the People’s Republic of China.

Name: INETYX
Description: INETYX propose au marché une technologie innovante selon le procédé breveté AMW (Additive Micro Welding).   Cette nouvelle technologie d'Impression 3D métal par micro soudure laser est en rupture avec les technologies d'Impression 3D SLM (Selective Laser Melting). Les matériaux poudres ont été remplacés par du fil. Les niveaux de précision et d'état de surface obtenus, en fin de fabrication, sont comparables à ceux réalisés par des procédés d'usinage. Grâce à l'imprimante 3D AMW300X, INETYX vous propose de partager son savoir-faire pour vous aider à atteindre vos objectifs industriels.   INETYX s'appuie sur l'expertise de son CEO Patrick TEULET, fort de 20 ans d'expériences acquises dans le domaine de l'Impression 3D métal.
